<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="147" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,625]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[317,494,393,417]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Leiostyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="beatae">
<emphasis box="[317,494,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">Leiostyla beatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been identified with 
<taxonomicName authority="Schileyko, 1975" authorityName="Schileyko" authorityYear="1975" box="[770,1146,393,417]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Leiostyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="silicea">
<emphasis box="[770,945,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">Leiostyla silicea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schileyko" box="[961,1137,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" refString="Schileyko, A. A. (1975) Mollyuski podsemeystva Lauriinae fauny SSSR (Pulmonata, Pupillidae). Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal, 54, 1767 - 1782." type="journal article" year="1975">
Schileyko, 
<number box="[1083,1137,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1161,1223,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[252,1326,194,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[252,1327,194,1775]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Shells of Leiostyla species. A – C. Leiostyla beatae n. sp., Georgia: Lagodekhishevi valley 2 km upstream of Lagodekhi; A. holotype (ZMH 101605); B. paratype (NHMW); C. paratype (ZMH 101606); D. Leiostyla silicea (Schileyko, 1975), Georgia: Tekhuri valley 6.7 km towards Lebarde (ZMH 86618); E. Leiostyla paulinae (Lindholm, 1913), Georgia: Kintrishi valley, Chakhati (ZMH 81306); F. Leiostyla caucasica (L. Pfeiffer, 1857), Georgia: Pasanauri, lower valley of Shavi Aragvi river (ZMH 81326). Scale bar = 1.0 mm for all figures except oblique view into aperture; scale bare = 0.5 mm for oblique view into aperture." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235957/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">
Fig. 
<number box="[1213,1223,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B) by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="146" refString="Pokryszko, B. M., Cameron, R. A. D., Mumladze, L. &amp; Tarkhnishvili, D. (2011) Forest snail faunas from Georgian Transcaucasia: patterns of diversity in a Pleistocene refugium. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 102, 239 - 250. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8312.2010.01575. x" type="journal article">
Pokryszko 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[197,254,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It differs from that species in the more cylindrical, lighter shell, the columellar lamella that is bending upwards and not running horizontally, and the lack of an upper palatal fold. Pilsbry (
<date box="[1071,1193,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" value="1922" valueMax="1923">
<number box="[1071,1193,464,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" value="1922.5" valueMax="1923.0" valueMin="1922.0">1922–1923</number>
</date>
) classified the species with a steeply ascending columellar lamella, namely 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindholm, 1913" authorityName="Lindholm" authorityYear="1913" box="[728,1128,497,521]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Leiostyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="paulinae">
<emphasis box="[728,927,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">Leiostyla paulinae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lindholm" box="[944,1120,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" refString="Lindholm, W. A. (1913) Beschreibung neuer Arten und Formen aus dem Kaukasus-Gebiete. Nachrichtsblatt der Deutschen Malakozoologischen Gesellschaft, 45, 17 - 23, 62 - 69." type="journal article" year="1913">
Lindholm, 
<number box="[1066,1120,498,521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" value="1913.0">1913</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. Pfeiffer, 1857" authorityName="L. Pfeiffer" authorityYear="1857" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Leiostyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis box="[1183,1396,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">Leiostyla caucasica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pfeiffer" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" refString="Pfeiffer, L. (1857) Neue Landschnecken. Malakozoologische Blatter, 4, 85 - 89." type="journal article" year="1857">
L. Pfeiffer, 
<number box="[245,302,533,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" value="1857.0">1857</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, in a separate section. The shape of the columellar lamella of 
<taxonomicName box="[987,1088,532,556]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Leiostyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="beatae">
<emphasis box="[987,1088,532,556]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">L. beatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of these species. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[261,362,567,591]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Leiostyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="beatae">
<emphasis box="[261,362,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">L. beatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[505,627,567,591]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Leiostyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="paulinae">
<emphasis box="[505,627,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">L. paulinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[642,703,568,591]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[252,1326,194,1774]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[252,1327,194,1775]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Shells of Leiostyla species. A – C. Leiostyla beatae n. sp., Georgia: Lagodekhishevi valley 2 km upstream of Lagodekhi; A. holotype (ZMH 101605); B. paratype (NHMW); C. paratype (ZMH 101606); D. Leiostyla silicea (Schileyko, 1975), Georgia: Tekhuri valley 6.7 km towards Lebarde (ZMH 86618); E. Leiostyla paulinae (Lindholm, 1913), Georgia: Kintrishi valley, Chakhati (ZMH 81306); F. Leiostyla caucasica (L. Pfeiffer, 1857), Georgia: Pasanauri, lower valley of Shavi Aragvi river (ZMH 81326). Scale bar = 1.0 mm for all figures except oblique view into aperture; scale bare = 0.5 mm for oblique view into aperture." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/235957/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">
Fig. 
<number box="[693,703,568,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C) in the cylindrical, more strongly rib-striated shell and the lack of an upper palatal fold and from 
<taxonomicName box="[481,615,602,625]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Leiostyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="146" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis box="[481,615,602,625]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="146">L. caucasica</emphasis>
